---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Aluminum Temper Designation Guide | Far East Metals" description="Comprehensive guide to aluminum temper designations including F, O, H, W, and T tempers. Learn about strain hardening, heat treatment, and aging processes for aluminum alloys.">
  <section class="temper-page page-section">
    <div class="content-card">

      <!-- Page Header -->
      <div class="page-header reveal">
        <svg class="header-svg" viewBox="0 0 400 160" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
          <!-- Furnace body -->
          <rect x="120" y="50" width="160" height="100" rx="8" fill="#888" stroke="#666" stroke-width="1.5"/>
          <rect x="130" y="58" width="140" height="75" rx="4" fill="#555" stroke="#444" stroke-width="1"/>
          <!-- Heat glow inside furnace -->
          <rect class="furnace-glow" x="130" y="58" width="140" height="75" rx="4" fill="#F5A623" opacity="0.15"/>
          <!-- Metal piece inside -->
          <g class="temper-metal">
            <rect x="165" y="90" width="70" height="25" rx="3" fill="#c0c0c0" stroke="#999" stroke-width="1.2"/>
            <rect x="165" y="90" width="70" height="7" rx="2" fill="#d8d8d8" opacity="0.5"/>
          </g>
          <!-- Heat waves -->
          <g class="heat-waves">
            <path d="M170 80 Q175 72 180 80" fill="none" stroke="#F5A623" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
            <path d="M190 75 Q195 65 200 75" fill="none" stroke="#e04040" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.5"/>
            <path d="M210 78 Q215 70 220 78" fill="none" stroke="#F5A623" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
          </g>
          <!-- Temperature gauge on right -->
          <rect x="290" y="60" width="12" height="80" rx="6" fill="#ddd" stroke="#bbb" stroke-width="1"/>
          <rect class="temp-fill" x="292" y="90" width="8" height="48" rx="4" fill="#e04040"/>
          <circle cx="296" cy="140" r="8" fill="#e04040" stroke="#bbb" stroke-width="1"/>
          <!-- Chimney -->
          <rect x="175" y="30" width="20" height="24" rx="2" fill="#777" stroke="#666" stroke-width="1"/>
          <!-- Smoke -->
          <g class="furnace-smoke">
            <circle cx="185" cy="22" r="5" fill="#ccc" opacity="0.4"/>
            <circle cx="180" cy="14" r="4" fill="#ccc" opacity="0.3"/>
            <circle cx="188" cy="6" r="3" fill="#ccc" opacity="0.2"/>
          </g>
        </svg>
        <h1 class="page-title">Aluminum Temper Designation Guide</h1>
        <p class="page-subtitle">Understanding temper designations is critical for selecting the right aluminum alloy condition for your application. This guide provides a complete reference to the Aluminum Association temper designation system, covering basic temper categories, subdivisions, and the metallurgical processes behind each designation.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 1: Temper System Overview / Flowchart -->
      <div class="section-block reveal">
        <h2 class="section-heading"><span class="section-num">01</span> Temper Designation System Overview</h2>
        <p>The temper designation follows the alloy number, separated by a hyphen (e.g., 6061-T6). It indicates the mechanical and thermal processing history that determines the material's final properties. The system consists of five basic temper categories.</p>

        <div class="flowchart-container">
          <div class="flowchart-root">
            <div class="flowchart-node root-node">Temper Designations</div>
            <div class="flowchart-trunk"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
            <div class="flowchart-hline"></div>
            <div class="flowchart-branches">

              <div class="flowchart-branch">
                <div class="flowchart-connector"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
                <div class="flowchart-node node-f" data-temper="f">F<span class="node-label">As Fabricated</span></div>
                <div class="sub-branches sub-desc">
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">No thermal or strain hardening control</div>
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">Billets, ingots, semi-finished products</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flowchart-branch">
                <div class="flowchart-connector"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
                <div class="flowchart-node node-o" data-temper="o">O<span class="node-label">Annealed</span></div>
                <div class="sub-branches sub-desc">
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">Lowest strength condition</div>
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">Maximum ductility &amp; workability</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flowchart-branch branch-h">
                <div class="flowchart-connector"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
                <div class="flowchart-node node-h" data-temper="h">H<span class="node-label">Strain Hardened</span></div>
                <div class="sub-branches">
                  <div class="sub-node">H1x<span>Strain hardened only</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">H2x<span>Partially annealed</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">H3x<span>Stabilized</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">H4x<span>Lacquered / painted</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flowchart-branch">
                <div class="flowchart-connector"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
                <div class="flowchart-node node-w" data-temper="w">W<span class="node-label">Solution Heat Treated</span></div>
                <div class="sub-branches sub-desc">
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">Unstable temper designation</div>
                  <div class="sub-node sub-note">Naturally ages over time</div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="flowchart-branch branch-t">
                <div class="flowchart-connector"><div class="connector-line"></div></div>
                <div class="flowchart-node node-t" data-temper="t">T<span class="node-label">Thermally Treated</span></div>
                <div class="sub-branches">
                  <div class="sub-node">T1&ndash;T2<span>Cooled from hot working</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">T3&ndash;T4<span>Natural aging</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">T5&ndash;T6<span>Artificially aged</span></div>
                  <div class="sub-node">T7&ndash;T10<span>Overaged / special</span></div>
                </div>
              </div>

            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2: F - As Fabricated -->
      <div class="section-block reveal">
        <h2 class="section-heading"><span class="section-num">02</span> F &mdash; As Fabricated</h2>
        <div class="content-card-inner">
          <div class="temper-detail-grid">
            <div class="temper-info">
              <h3>Definition</h3>
              <p>The F temper applies to products shaped by cold working, hot working, or casting processes where no special control over thermal conditions or strain hardening is employed. There are no mechanical property limits specified for this temper.</p>
              <h3>When Used</h3>
              <p>F temper is used for products where subsequent forming or machining will take place, or where the as-fabricated properties are adequate for the intended application. Common in billets, ingots, and semi-finished products destined for further processing.</p>
              <h3>Key Properties</h3>
              <ul class="prop-list">
                <li>No guaranteed mechanical properties</li>
                <li>Properties vary based on manufacturing process</li>
                <li>Not suitable for structural applications requiring defined properties</li>
                <li>Cost-effective for intermediate products</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="temper-svg-container">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 280 200" class="process-svg" aria-label="As fabricated process illustration">
                <!-- Production line -->
                <rect x="20" y="130" width="240" height="8" rx="4" fill="#ddd" stroke="#bbb" stroke-width="1"/>
                <!-- Rollers -->
                <circle cx="60" cy="130" r="12" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2">
                  <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="0 60 130" to="360 60 130" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </circle>
                <circle cx="60" cy="130" r="3" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.5"/>
                <circle cx="120" cy="130" r="12" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2">
                  <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="0 120 130" to="360 120 130" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </circle>
                <circle cx="120" cy="130" r="3" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.5"/>
                <!-- Material moving across the line -->
                <rect y="118" width="40" height="12" rx="2" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.7">
                  <animate attributeName="x" values="0;240;0" dur="5s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </rect>
                <!-- Label -->
                <text x="140" y="80" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-title)" font-size="14" fill="#444">Raw Material</text>
                <text x="140" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-main)" font-size="11" fill="#888">No controlled thermal or mechanical treatment</text>
                <!-- Arrow -->
                <line x1="140" y1="104" x2="140" y2="115" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-dasharray="3,2"/>
                <polygon points="136,115 144,115 140,120" fill="var(--color-accent)"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3: O - Annealed -->
      <div class="section-block reveal">
        <h2 class="section-heading"><span class="section-num">03</span> O &mdash; Annealed</h2>
        <div class="content-card-inner">
          <div class="temper-detail-grid">
            <div class="temper-info">
              <h3>Definition</h3>
              <p>The O temper designates wrought products that have been annealed to obtain the lowest strength condition, providing maximum ductility and workability. For cast products, O denotes annealing to improve ductility and dimensional stability.</p>
              <h3>Process</h3>
              <p>The material is heated to a specified temperature (typically 340&ndash;415&deg;C for most aluminum alloys), held at that temperature for a sufficient time to allow complete recrystallization, then slowly cooled (furnace cooled or controlled cooling at &le;28&deg;C/hr) to prevent any re-hardening.</p>
              <h3>Key Properties</h3>
              <ul class="prop-list">
                <li>Lowest tensile and yield strength</li>
                <li>Maximum elongation and formability</li>
                <li>Excellent for deep drawing and severe forming operations</li>
                <li>Fully recrystallized grain structure</li>
              </ul>
              <h3>Typical Applications</h3>
              <p>Sheet metal for deep drawing, complex stampings, cookware blanks, heat exchanger fins, and any application requiring maximum formability.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="temper-svg-container">
              <!-- Annealing process SVG -->
              <svg viewBox="0 0 280 220" class="process-svg" aria-label="Annealing process: heating, holding, slow cooling">
                <!-- Furnace body -->
                <rect x="30" y="60" width="100" height="80" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2"/>
                <text x="80" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-title)" font-size="11" fill="#888">FURNACE</text>
                <!-- Heat waves -->
                <path d="M50,85 Q55,80 60,85 Q65,90 70,85" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6">
                  <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0.3;0.8;0.3" dur="1.5s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                  <animate attributeName="d" values="M50,85 Q55,80 60,85 Q65,90 70,85;M50,80 Q55,75 60,80 Q65,85 70,80;M50,85 Q55,80 60,85 Q65,90 70,85" dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </path>
                <path d="M55,100 Q60,95 65,100 Q70,105 75,100" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.5">
                  <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0.5;1;0.5" dur="1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </path>
                <path d="M60,115 Q65,110 70,115 Q75,120 80,115" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.4">
                  <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0.4;0.9;0.4" dur="2.2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </path>
                <!-- Material inside furnace -->
                <rect x="60" y="90" width="40" height="16" rx="3" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.8"/>
                <!-- Temperature label -->
                <text x="80" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-main)" font-size="10" fill="#e74c3c">340&ndash;415&deg;C</text>

                <!-- Arrow to cooling -->
                <line x1="135" y1="100" x2="155" y2="100" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                <polygon points="155,96 163,100 155,104" fill="var(--color-accent)"/>

                <!-- Slow cooling -->
                <rect x="168" y="60" width="90" height="80" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="#3498db" stroke-width="2"/>
                <text x="213" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-title)" font-size="11" fill="#888">SLOW COOL</text>
                <!-- Cooling arrows (downward) -->
                <line x1="195" y1="80" x2="195" y2="120" stroke="#3498db" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3,3">
                  <animate attributeName="stroke-dashoffset" values="0;-12" dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </line>
                <line x1="213" y1="80" x2="213" y2="120" stroke="#3498db" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3,3">
                  <animate attributeName="stroke-dashoffset" values="0;-12" dur="2.3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </line>
                <line x1="231" y1="80" x2="231" y2="120" stroke="#3498db" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="3,3">
                  <animate attributeName="stroke-dashoffset" values="0;-12" dur="1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
                </line>
                <!-- Material cooling -->
                <rect x="193" y="92" width="40" height="16" rx="3" fill="#3498db" opacity="0.5"/>
                <text x="213" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-main)" font-size="10" fill="#3498db">&le;28&deg;C/hr</text>

                <!-- Temperature curve -->
                <text x="140" y="175" text-anchor="middle" font-family="var(--font-title)" font-size="11" fill="#888">TEMPERATURE PROFILE</text>
                <line x1="40" y1="210" x2="250" y2="210" stroke="#ccc" stroke-width="1"/>
                <line x1="40" y1="190" x2="40" y2="210" stroke="#ccc" stroke-width="1"/>
                <path class="temp-curve" d="M40,210 L70,188 L140,188 L250,208" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <text x="30" y="190" font-size="8" fill="#888">T</text>
                <text x="250" y="208" font-size="8" fill="#888">t</text>
              </svg>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4: H - Strain Hardened -->
      <div class="section-block reveal">
        <h2 class="section-heading"><span class="section-num">04</span> H &mdash; Strain Hardened</h2>
        <p class="section-intro">The H temper applies to wrought products that have been strengthened through strain hardening (cold working), with or without supplementary thermal treatment. This designation is used exclusively for <strong>non-heat-treatable alloys</strong> in the 1xxx, 3xxx, and 5xxx series.</p>

        <!-- H1x -->
        <div class="content-card-inner h-sub-section reveal">
          <h3>H1x &mdash; Strain Hardened Only</h3>
          <p>Products that are strain hardened to obtain the desired strength without any supplementary thermal treatment. The second digit indicates the degree of strain hardening.</p>
          <div class="h-degree-grid">
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H12</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/4 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill" data-width="25"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H14</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/2 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill" data-width="50"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H16</span>
              <span class="degree-name">3/4 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill" data-width="75"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H18</span>
              <span class="degree-name">Full Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill" data-width="100"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H19</span>
              <span class="degree-name">Extra Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill" data-width="110"></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Cold rolling SVG -->
          <div class="temper-svg-container svg-wide">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 400 140" class="process-svg" aria-label="Cold rolling strain hardening process">
              <!-- Top roller -->
              <circle cx="200" cy="40" r="28" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2">
                <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="0 200 40" to="360 200 40" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </circle>
              <circle cx="200" cy="40" r="5" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.4"/>
              <line x1="200" y1="12" x2="200" y2="28" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
              <line x1="200" y1="52" x2="200" y2="68" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.3"/>
              <!-- Bottom roller -->
              <circle cx="200" cy="108" r="28" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="2">
                <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="360 200 108" to="0 200 108" dur="3s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </circle>
              <circle cx="200" cy="108" r="5" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.4"/>
              <!-- Incoming material (thick) -->
              <rect x="30" y="62" width="145" height="24" rx="2" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.5"/>
              <text x="100" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#888" font-family="var(--font-main)">Thick stock</text>
              <!-- Outgoing material (thin) -->
              <rect x="225" y="68" width="145" height="12" rx="2" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.7"/>
              <text x="300" y="62" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#888" font-family="var(--font-main)">Strain hardened</text>
              <!-- Arrows -->
              <line x1="50" y1="74" x2="168" y2="74" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3">
                <animate attributeName="stroke-dashoffset" values="0;-14" dur="1s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </line>
              <line x1="232" y1="74" x2="360" y2="74" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1" opacity="0.5" stroke-dasharray="4,3">
                <animate attributeName="stroke-dashoffset" values="0;-14" dur="1s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </line>
              <!-- Pressure arrows -->
              <line x1="200" y1="2" x2="200" y2="10" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="2"/>
              <polygon points="196,10 204,10 200,14" fill="#e74c3c"/>
              <line x1="200" y1="146" x2="200" y2="138" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="2"/>
              <polygon points="196,138 204,138 200,134" fill="#e74c3c"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- H2x -->
        <div class="content-card-inner h-sub-section reveal">
          <h3>H2x &mdash; Strain Hardened &amp; Partially Annealed</h3>
          <p>Products that are strain hardened more than the desired final amount, then reduced in strength to the desired level by partial annealing. This process results in slightly better ductility than H1x at the same strength level.</p>
          <div class="h-degree-grid">
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H22</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/4 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h2-fill" data-width="25"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H24</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/2 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h2-fill" data-width="50"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H26</span>
              <span class="degree-name">3/4 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h2-fill" data-width="75"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H28</span>
              <span class="degree-name">Full Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h2-fill" data-width="100"></div></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Partial anneal process SVG -->
          <div class="temper-svg-container svg-wide">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 400 120" class="process-svg" aria-label="Strain hardening then partial annealing process">
              <!-- Step 1: Cold work -->
              <rect x="10" y="35" width="100" height="50" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="60" y="30" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="var(--color-accent)" font-family="var(--font-title)">1. COLD WORK</text>
              <circle cx="40" cy="52" r="10" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5">
                <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="0 40 52" to="360 40 52" dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </circle>
              <circle cx="40" cy="72" r="10" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5">
                <animateTransform attributeName="transform" type="rotate" from="360 40 72" to="0 40 72" dur="2s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </circle>
              <rect x="55" y="57" width="50" height="10" rx="2" fill="var(--color-accent)" opacity="0.5"/>
              <!-- Arrow -->
              <line x1="115" y1="60" x2="140" y2="60" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <polygon points="140,56 148,60 140,64" fill="var(--color-accent)"/>
              <!-- Step 2: Partial anneal -->
              <rect x="153" y="35" width="100" height="50" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="203" y="30" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#e74c3c" font-family="var(--font-title)">2. PARTIAL ANNEAL</text>
              <path d="M170,55 Q175,50 180,55 Q185,60 190,55" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6">
                <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0.3;0.8;0.3" dur="1.5s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </path>
              <path d="M205,55 Q210,50 215,55 Q220,60 225,55" fill="none" stroke="#e74c3c" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6">
                <animate attributeName="opacity" values="0.5;1;0.5" dur="1.8s" repeatCount="indefinite"/>
              </path>
              <rect x="178" y="65" width="50" height="10" rx="2" fill="#e74c3c" opacity="0.3"/>
              <!-- Arrow -->
              <line x1="258" y1="60" x2="283" y2="60" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <polygon points="283,56 291,60 283,64" fill="var(--color-accent)"/>
              <!-- Result -->
              <rect x="296" y="35" width="94" height="50" rx="6" fill="none" stroke="#27ae60" stroke-width="1.5"/>
              <text x="343" y="30" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#27ae60" font-family="var(--font-title)">RESULT</text>
              <text x="343" y="58" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#444" font-family="var(--font-main)">Desired</text>
              <text x="343" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#444" font-family="var(--font-main)">strength</text>
              <!-- Bottom label -->
              <text x="200" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#888" font-family="var(--font-main)">Better ductility than H1x at same strength level</text>
            </svg>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- H3x -->
        <div class="content-card-inner h-sub-section reveal">
          <h3>H3x &mdash; Strain Hardened &amp; Stabilized</h3>
          <p>Products that are strain hardened and then stabilized by a low-temperature thermal treatment. This process is applied to alloys (particularly Mg-containing 5xxx series) that gradually age-soften at room temperature. The stabilization locks in the mechanical properties so they do not change over time.</p>
          <div class="h-degree-grid">
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H32</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/4 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h3-fill" data-width="25"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H34</span>
              <span class="degree-name">1/2 Hard</span>
              <div class="strength-bar"><div class="strength-fill h3-fill" data-width="50"></div></div>
            </div>
            <div class="h-degree">
              <span class="degree-code">H36</span>
              <span class="degree-name">3/4 Hard</span>
