        <div class="comparison-grid">

          <!-- 6063-T5 vs 6063-T6 -->
          <div class="comparison-card content-card-inner reveal" data-comparison="6063">
            <h3>6063-T5 vs 6063-T6</h3>
            <p class="comp-subtitle">Architectural extrusions: air quench vs water quench</p>
            <div class="comp-bars">
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Yield Strength</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T5</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="55" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>145 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T6</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="82" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>215 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">UTS</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T5</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="62" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>185 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T6</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="80" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>240 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Elongation</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T5</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="60" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>8%</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">T6</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="72" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>12%</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="comp-note">T6 requires a separate solution heat treatment step with water quench, adding cost. T5 is preferred for non-structural architectural applications where lower strength is acceptable.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- 6061-T6 vs 7075-T6 -->
          <div class="comparison-card content-card-inner reveal">
            <h3>6061-T6 vs 7075-T6</h3>
            <p class="comp-subtitle">General structural vs high-strength aerospace</p>
            <div class="comp-bars">
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Yield Strength</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">6061</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="49" style="--cbar-color:#27ae60;"><span>275 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">7075</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="90" style="--cbar-color:#e74c3c;"><span>505 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">UTS</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">6061</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="54" style="--cbar-color:#27ae60;"><span>310 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">7075</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="100" style="--cbar-color:#e74c3c;"><span>570 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Corrosion Resistance</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">6061</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="90" style="--cbar-color:#27ae60;"><span>Excellent</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">7075</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="40" style="--cbar-color:#e74c3c;"><span>Fair</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="comp-note">7075-T6 offers nearly twice the strength of 6061-T6 but at the expense of weldability and corrosion resistance. 6061-T6 is readily weldable and far more versatile for general engineering use. 7075 is the standard for aerospace structural members, while 6061 dominates in general structural, marine, and transportation applications.</p>
          </div>

          <!-- 5052-H32 vs 5052-O -->
          <div class="comparison-card content-card-inner reveal">
            <h3>5052-H32 vs 5052-O</h3>
            <p class="comp-subtitle">Strain hardened vs annealed (non-heat-treatable)</p>
            <div class="comp-bars">
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Yield Strength</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">H32</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="78" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>195 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">O</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="36" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>90 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">UTS</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">H32</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="80" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>230 MPa</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">O</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="55" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>195 MPa</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="comp-row">
                <span class="comp-label">Elongation</span>
                <div class="comp-bar-pair">
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">H32</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="50" style="--cbar-color:var(--color-accent);"><span>12%</span></div></div>
                  <div class="comp-bar-wrap"><span class="comp-tag">O</span><div class="comp-bar" data-width="90" style="--cbar-color:#3498db;"><span>25%</span></div></div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="comp-note">5052-O offers maximum formability and is ideal for deep drawing and spinning. 5052-H32 provides roughly double the yield strength with good corrosion resistance, commonly used for marine applications, fuel tanks, and sheet metal work where moderate forming is needed.</p>
          </div>

